
<div class='container'>
  <div class='jumbotron'>
    <h1>Daru::IO | Daru::View</h1>
    <p>
      This site contains demonstration of two gems, accompanying <a href="https://github.com/sciruby/daru">daru</a>
      data analysis gem:
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-success" href="https://github.com/Sciruby/daru-io" role="button">daru-io</a></p>
        <p class="text-muted">A set of independent importers/exporters from various data sources and formats.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-success" href="https://github.com/Sciruby/daru-view" role="button">daru-view</a></p>
        <p class="text-muted">A set of view helpers for web frameworks, for pretty representations of data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h1>Available examples</h1>
  <p class="text-muted">All examples are demonstrating charts and tables from <mark>daru-view</mark>, and different techniques from <mark>daru-io</mark>.</p>

  <div class="alert alert-info">BTW, to show this table we also use <code>Daru::DataFrame</code> and <code>daru_table</code> helper</div>

  <div class="view-and-code">
    <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
      <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#view" aria-controls="view" role="tab" data-toggle="view">View</a></li>
      <li role="presentation"><a href="#code" aria-controls="code" role="tab" data-toggle="code">Code</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tab-content">
      <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="view">
        <%=
          daru_table(@links,
            adapter: :datatables, height: 500, width: 700,
            paging: false, searching: false, info: false
          )
        %>
      </div>
      <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="code">
        <%= rouge(%{
          daru_table(@links,
            adapter: :datatables, height: 500, width: 700,
            paging: false, searching: false, info: false
          )
        }) %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
